arStrings.szText: The hairs on the back of my neck stood when I heard the first whispered hiss. Quickly my mind took me to fear. The next hiss was methodical and gentle, the hairs fell, and I listened.
Voice getting more and more disturbed. A haunted feeling.
“Follow us for succor, your peril will heal.” These whispers are truth, I tell you, they have found comfort in the walls of my skull.

I must find the source.  I must find the source.  I must find the source.  

The whispers.  My relief.
